when installing cuda on ubuntu make sure to match the cuda version with the ubuntu kernel version. e.g. on Ubuntu 16, kernel-4.4 is a requirement. 

To remove the older kernel version
    sudo apt-get purge linux-headers-<kernel-version> 
    sudo apt-get purge linux-image-<kernel-version> 
    sudo apt-get install linux-headers-<kernel-version-required> 
    sudo atp-get install linux-image-<kernel-version-required> 


